<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <!-- Google Fonts -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- Material Icons -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- Base CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/variables.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/global.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    
    <style>
        .privacy-header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 50%, #0f172a 100%);
            color: #fff;
            padding: 4rem 2rem 5rem;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        }
        .privacy-title {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #fff, #94a3b8);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }
        .privacy-content {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: -3rem auto 4rem;
            background: var(--color-bg-primary);
            border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
            padding: 3rem;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 10;
        }
        .privacy-section {
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        }
        .privacy-section h2 {
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            color: var(--color-text-primary);
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .privacy-section p, .privacy-section li {
            color: var(--color-text-secondary);
            line-height: 1.7;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }
        .privacy-section ul {
            padding-left: 1.5rem;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }
        .privacy-section li {
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .back-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            color: #94a3b8;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }
        .back-link:hover {
            color: #fff;
        }
        
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .privacy-content {
                padding: 1.5rem;
                margin: -2rem 1rem 3rem;
            }
            .privacy-title {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="theme-dark">

    <div class="privacy-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link"><span class="material-icons">arrow_back</span> Back to Home</a>
        <h1 class="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p style="color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.9rem;">Effective Date: <span id="effective-date"></span></p>
    </div>

    <main class="container">
        <div class="privacy-content">
            <p class="mb-xl text-secondary" style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.6;">
                This Privacy Policy outlines how the Los Santos Department of Justice (LSDOJ) Case Filing System, developed by KWTS, collects, uses, and protects your information when you visit and use our website. This Website only intended for the Mobtown Fivem Server.
            </p>

            <div class="privacy-section">
                <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>To maintain system security and manage user access, we collect a strictly limited amount of data. When you access or register for our system, we collect the following:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> When you visit the website, our servers automatically record standard log data. This includes your IP address and your browser type/version (User-Agent string).</li>
                    <li><strong>Account Request Information:</strong> When you request an account to access the case filing system, we collect the specific information you voluntarily provide in the application form (e.g., your roleplay name, Discord ID, or other necessary community identifiers).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="privacy-section">
                <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>The information we collect is used solely for the administration and security of the roleplay community's hobby project:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>To Manage Accounts:</strong> The information provided during the account request process is used to verify your identity within the community, grant proper system permissions, and manage your access to the filing system.</li>
                    <li><strong>To Maintain Security:</strong> Your IP address and browser information are logged to detect and prevent unauthorized access, malicious activity, or abuse of the website.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="privacy-section">
                <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
                <p>We respect your privacy. We do not sell, trade, rent, or share your personal information with third parties, external advertisers, or organizations outside of our community's administrative team. Your data is accessible only to KWTS, authorized server administrators, and developers for system maintenance and moderation purposes.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="privacy-section">
                <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
                <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect the limited data we collect from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, please remember that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="privacy-section">
                <h2>5. Your Consent</h2>
                <p>By using this website and submitting an account request, you consent to our collection and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy, and you acknowledge that you have read and understood the Roleplay Disclaimer.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="privacy-section">
                <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
                <p>If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, your data, or the system itself, please contact the development team or community management via mobtown DOJ discord server.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer_full') %>

    <script src="/js/theme.js"></script>
    <script>
        document.getElementById('effective-date').textContent = new Date().toLocaleDateString();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
